naointerface.main

Class BodyParts

  • java.lang.Object
    • naointerface.main.BodyParts

  • public final class BodyParts
extends java.lang.Object
    This utility class consist all the names for the Bodyparts of a Nao robot, that are used in the JNaoQi API. Some of them are marked with a @Supported annotation.

    The list naointerface.main.BodyParts.BODY_PARTS consists all the fields that are in this class that are NOT marked with a @NoBodyPart annotation.
    The list naointerface.main.BodyParts.SUPPORTED_BODY_PARTS consists all the fields that are in this class that are marked with a @Supported annotation.
    Bodyparts that are marked with the @Supported annotation can be used to invoke the constructor of the class naointerface.main.Move.
    Author:
    Nelli Welker, Etienne Onasch

      • getBodyParts

        private static java.util.List<java.lang.String> getBodyParts(boolean supportedOnly)
        Returns a List of all BodyParts with Reflections.
        Parameters:
        supportedOnly - If true, this method returns a list of the supported BodyParts only!
        The methods moveAbsolute(...) and moveRelative(...) from a Nao instance
        only work with supported BodyParts!
        If true, a list of all BodyParts is returned.
        Returns:
        the list of BodyParts
